South African Mines Department Raided Over Anglo Rights Dispute, 702 Says

-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 
2011-07-27T13:40:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-27/south-african-mines-department-raided-over-anglo-rights-dispute-702-says.html
South Africa ’s special police
investigating unit, known as the Hawks, raided offices of the
Department of Mineral Resources, Imperial Crown Trading 289 Ltd.
and the State Attorney, Talk Radio 702 reported, without saying
where it got the information.   The Hawks are investigating claims that fraudulent
documents were central to a legal dispute over the Sishen Iron
Ore Co., the Johannesburg-based radio station said.   Hawks spokesman McIntosh Polela didn’t answer calls to
either of his mobile phones today.   Jagdish Parekh, a shareholder of ICT, declined to comment
today when Bloomberg News reached him on his mobile phone,
referring queries to ICT Chief Executive Officer Phemelo
Sehunelo, who referred queries to the company’s lawyers when
contacted by mobile phone.   Mineral Resources spokeswoman Zingapi Jakuja couldn’t
immediately comment when Bloomberg reached her on her mobile
phone. Tlali Tlali, spokesman for the  Department of Justice ,
didn’t answer calls to his mobile phone, which wasn’t taking
messages.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Carli Lourens at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net  